/* 
Using bitwise operations, 
implement the C0 function opacify(p) 
that returns the result of making the pixel p totally opaque 
(i.e., setting its alpha value to 255, while retaining the values of the color
channels). 
Assume that the pixels are represented as ints.
*/

int opacify(int p)
{
    int mask_opa = 0xFF000000;
    return (p | mask_opa);
}